paragraphs.title: Load Data / Create Model / Train
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.commons.io.IOUtils
import java.net.URL
import java.nio.charset.Charset
import org.apache.spark.mllib.regression.LabeledPoint
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.ProbabilisticClassifier
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.LogisticRegression
import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.MulticlassMetrics
import org.apache.spark.mllib.util.MLUtils
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler
import org.apache.spark.ml.linalg.Vectors
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.BinaryClassificationMetrics
import org.apache.spark.mllib.classification.LogisticRegressionWithLBFGS
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.{BinaryLogisticRegressionSummary, LogisticRegression}

// Load training data

val dataText = sc.parallelize(
    IOUtils.toString(
        new URL("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hortonworks-gallery/zeppelin-notebooks/master/2D8S9EJ23/training.csv"),
        Charset.forName("utf8")).split("\n"))

case class Data(label: Integer, accountNumber: Integer, distance: Double, category: Double, frequency: Double, transaction: Double)
val r = scala.util.Random
val data = dataText.map(s => s.split(",")).filter(s => s(0) != "\"label\"").map(
    s => Data(s(0).toInt,
            s(1).replaceAll("\"", "").toInt,
            s(2).replaceAll("\"", "").toDouble,
            s(3).replaceAll("\"", "").toDouble,
            s(4).replaceAll("\"", "").toDouble,
            r.nextDouble
        )
).toDF()
data.registerTempTable("data")
data.printSchema
data.show

// create feature vector
val assembler =  new VectorAssembler().setInputCols(Array("distance", "category", "frequency")).setOutputCol("features")
  
// assemble a new vector from dataframe
val df1 = assembler.transform(data).select($"label", $"features")

// Split the data into train and test
val splits = df1.randomSplit(Array(7.0, 3.0), seed = 1234L)
val (train, test) = (splits(0), splits(1))

// create model
val model = new LogisticRegression().setMaxIter(700).setRegParam(0.1).setElasticNetParam(0.8)
//.setFamily("binomial")

// train model
val rModel = model.fit(train)

// Print the coefficients and intercepts for logistic regression with multinomial family
//println(s"Multinomial coefficients: ${rModel.coefficientMatrix}")
//println(s"Multinomial intercepts: ${rModel.interceptVector}")
